sec.p:
Ten professionals expressed interest in the focus groups and seven (3 M, 4 F) attended one of two groups (one group had five participants and the other, two). Focus group participants worked in a range of settings, varied across the groups and were geographically spread across the United Kingdom. The first focus group was comprised of two paediatric consultants (both with clinical experience with CYP with Long Covid), one nurse consultant (Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services), one physiotherapist (adult pain and Long Covid services) and a primary school teacher. The second focus group was made up of a physiotherapist (Children's Long Covid hub
1
) and a GP.
